ds Committee members were provided with a copy of the ad that went in", "the newspaper this week. Committee members to provide any ideas for the next ACTION:", "newspaper ad to L. Webb.", "\u2013 5.5. Speaker Series Will begin speaker series in November. Any recommendation ACTION:", "for speakers pass along to L. Webb.", "Senior\u2019s Fair \u2013 5.6. Noted United Way is the organizing group. Committee members discussed", "partnering with PROBUS and/or Revera - The Village to provide transportation to the", "Senior\u2019s Fair rather than repeating the same event here.", "6. ROUNDTABLE", "6.1. D. Adams noted concern with vehicle speed on 10th street and not watching for people", "walking/crossing the road. L. Webb to invite Police Chief Knoll to a future ACTION:", "meeting.", "6.2. N. Graham noted upcoming Library events including October 3 author reading by John", "Gardiner and November 3 author reading by Dr. Gregory Klages. Chamber is looking for", "any suggestions on businesses in town that would be good candidates for the ramp grant", "program.", "6.3. Committee member is looking for suggestions for \u2018meals on wheels\u2019 type program. L.", "Webb suggested contacting Home and Community Support Services.", "6.4. It was noted that there are taxi discounts for seniors in other communities and was", "wondering if any of our local taxis offer anything similar.", "\u2013 Tuesday, October 16, 2018 l 2:00 pm 7. NEXT MEETING", "P & H Centre Boardroom", "8. ADJOURNMENT", "Moved by N. Graham", "THAT the meeting adjourned at 3:30 pm", "___________________________________________", "Committee Chair", "___________________________________________", "Sherri Walden, Director of Parks, Recreation & Culture", "AGE-FRIENDLY COMMITTEE MINUTES | PAGE 2"], "bbox": [[0.175131, 0.043197, 0.6274979999999999, 0.019264], [0.175131, 0.059258, 0.41323699999999997, 0.019153], [0.304542, 0.092756, -0.13799299999999998, 0.017317], [0.175131, 0.091227, 0.685265, 0.019153], [0.175131, 0.10